%N A327602 A chess knight starts at 1 on an extended multiplication table and moves to the next perfect power such that 1) the number of jumps is minimized and 2) the sum of the intermediate numbers is minimized. In case of a tie, choose the lexicographically earliest path.
%e A327602 Between 4 and 8, the shortest route is through 12 (2*6); it takes only two steps:
